Summary:

Aziraphale has a problem and Crowley rises to the occasion. Or: the one where they have a baby.

*

Crowley felt a dart of foreboding. Uncomfortably, he reached out with a tendril of power and read her body. She was definitely wholly female, even now, everything that a human would have between her legs and below her navel.

And then. Something else. Something extra. No larger than an apple seed.  

He leaned back against the door frame and stared at the ceiling.

“Ah.”

“Quite.”

“You’re…”

“Yes.”

“That’s unfortunate,” he admitted.

Aziraphale let out a noise that wasn’t a laugh, and yet. “Yes, thank you, Crowley, I’m aware.”

summary: with how long azira holds on to clothes (according to neilman) all his stuff must be so soft and smell so much like him by now....
body:
with how long azira holds on to clothes (according to neilman) all his stuff must be so soft and smell so much like him by now. you know how that kinda happens with your old, worn out shirts? azira’s closet must be stock-full of good-enough-to-sleep in soft shirts. and can you imagine how good they must smell? if he’s the type to launder them manually that is, instead of magic-ing them clean. his detergent and his own natural scent must have infused so well with the fibers by now that even wearing them for a long time won’t be enough for it to fade.

i just imagine crowley stealing a shirt or so and using them as pajamas or just around his flat during those times he doesn’t see azira as often as he would like. he returns them once azira decides to change though (because he does so so rarely, ya know? why bother changing on weeks when all he would see are either stray customers or crowley?), and that’s why azira’s wardrobe doesn’t shrink despite how many garments crowley traffics between their closets.

and can you imagine hugging him with his soft clothes? he’s already so huggable with all that extra pudge on him but can you imagine that plus the softness and pleasant, warm scent that comes with well worn clothing?????

soft!aziraphale is basically what i’m saying here. soft!aziraphale is my jam.

summary: Okay, but - Crowley calling Aziraphale ‘cherub’, though. When Aziraphale’s expounding on something, slightly pink-cheeked on...
body:
Okay, but - Crowley calling Aziraphale ‘cherub’, though. When Aziraphale’s expounding on something, slightly pink-cheeked on afternoon wine, and Crowley’s watching affectionately and has gotten the point:

“All right, cherub.”

This occasions a frown. “I’ve told you not to call me that.”

“But you look just like one.”

“I most certainly do not.” Glasses are pushed up the nose. “One face, Crowley. Just the one. And one set of wings. Not to mention that cherubic duties are far above my pay-grade. The very idea–”

“You’ve got rosy cheeks and blond curls. Ask Raphael. Ask anyone. That’s a cherub.”

“That’s a putto. And quite frankly, a rather unlikely depiction of any type of Heavenly messenger. Really, we’ve gone through this before, and I sometimes think, although I hate to say it, that you’re choosing to ignore me.”

“All right, then. Not a cherub. An angel.”

“A Principality–”

“Of course. Come here, Principality.”

Hello, I'm tinsnip.

Feeling rather ineffable these days. Expect a great deal of Good Omens.

Other interests: Star Trek. (Primarily DS9 and Cardassians.)
Pratchett. Wodehouse.
Cats. The Doctors Whom. Science. Cute things. Life truths. Pixels. And spiders, sometimes, so keep that in mind.

I post fic on AO3. It's quite good - you should have a look.

My work with Vyc on a Kardasi conlang is here.

Cardassian meta is found mostly under cardassians or kardasi.

If you enjoy my fanfic, why not buy me a coffee?
